&lt;div id="a-tribute" class="section level2"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A Tribute!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since the dawn of time, people have been developing human-like attachments to their transportation. I imagine Moses naming his chariot, Noah his ark, and maybe even Jesus naming his borrowed donkey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Well, maybe I’m taking too much historical license, but man’s affinity for their transportation remains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the age of 21, my dad and I split the cost of a 2005 Ford F150. The odometer read ~24,000 miles and it set us back ~$20,000.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>